# 10 — Still capture in-flight guard
# Actor isolation replaces a lock via synchronous guard+set before first await.
# Cross-ref: design/02-concurrency.md §Invariant 7

shape: sequence_diagram

VM: CameraViewModel
SC: "StillCaptureController\n(actor)"
APO: AVCapturePhotoOutput
EX: EXIFWriter
FS: FileSystem

First capture call — actor is idle: {
  VM -> SC: "await captureNaturalPicture()"
  SC -> SC: "guard !captureInFlight else throw INVALID_STATE\n(synchronous — before any await)"
  SC -> SC: "captureInFlight = true"
  SC -> SC: "defer { captureInFlight = false }"
  SC -> APO: "capturePhoto(with: settings, delegate: self)\n(await suspension point)"
}

Second capture call arrives while first is in-flight: {
  VM -> SC: "await captureNaturalPicture()  [concurrent]"
  SC -> SC: "guard !captureInFlight\ncaptureInFlight == true ⇒ throw"
  SC -> VM: "throw CameraError(.invalidState)"
}

First capture's photo delivery resumes: {
  APO -> SC: didFinishProcessingPhoto (delegate)
  SC -> SC: receive AVCapturePhoto
  SC -> EX: buildEXIFProperties(sensor metadata)
  EX -> SC: CFDictionary of EXIF tags
  SC -> FS: write JPEG to temp URL
  SC -> EX: "CGImageDestinationAddImageFromSource\nwith EXIF dict"
  FS -> SC: path
  SC -> VM: "return path\n(defer fires: captureInFlight = false)"
}
